<br>
When I build groups, I frequently will start casting for what I need to fill the group.  If we need a cleric for Sebilis and can't find one in zone or through the guilds of the other groupmembers, I'll start doing /who all cleric polls for various level ranges and will eventually end up asking every unanon Cleric on Kunark if he is in need of a group.  If I can't find any I'll check for druids or shaman.  There is no reason for anyone to ever ask a mage like this.<br>
<br>
When I played my warrior, I would get hit up like this out of the blue plenty.  Someone is trying to make a group, but they need a tank.  People <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> really want</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> classes like warriors.  They fill a vital mission.<br>
<br>
There is no <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> need</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for a mage.<br>
<br>
So no, it's really not a social problem at all.  It's a class balance problem.  Wizards have the same issue.  Really, Verant not liking AE groups is rather funny, because I'm pretty sure it's the class imbalance that brought them about: all these LFG wizards and mages with nothing better to do than try to group with each other.<br>
<br>
And yes, it's all very keen to keep telling everyone to make their own groups, but, and this may shock you, not everyone likes making and leading groups.  If you've only ever played a magician, then you're missing out: plenty of other classes never have to worry about making groups.  I rarely made my own group with my warrior.  There was no need.  Saying &quot;Hello&quot; in guildchat was usually enough to get me a group.  I'd like to tell you this was because of my charming personality, but I'd say it had quite a lot more to do with the fact that I was playing a vital class.<br>
<br>
On Stormhammer during primetime there is always fewer than 40 unanon magicians online.  (/who all magician 1 50 usually reveals about 15-20 and /who all magician 51 59 another 15-20).  For such a tiny population, it's frankly amazing how often I end up in a group with another magician.<br>
<br>
So yes, magicians finding groups can definiately be an issue.  Your only real hope is to be in a good guild of friends.  Friends who will invite you to group, even though they'd be better off with a more powerful class.<br>
