<br>
Again, these counter arguments indicate an unfamiliarity with social sciences in general, and with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Social Psychology</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Anthropology</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in particular.<br>
<br>
If you examined your own biases, you might learn that much of what you think you know is instead shared assumptions.<br>
<br>
I don't deny that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have some problems.  I do deny that the problems that many <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> face in getting groups is based entirely or even mostly on an unbiased and wholly objective analysis of the game and its apparent consequences.<br>
<br>
The fact that other classes may be more popular than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in no way refutes my proposition that grouping is primarily a social issue, just as the ease at which I personally get groups is not a refutation of the existance of serious class balance issues for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in general.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#333333>(3/25/02 8:59:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=163.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Grouping IS a social issue!</span><hr size=1> Raz<br>
<br>
Even though I believe you mean well I kinda think you are not agreeing just to not agree. I play a bard and a mage as my two main characters. I am very social and get along with most people in EQ. I have alot of friends and it is one of the reasons I continue to play. I have very little problems getting a group as my bard. A perfect example is tonight in Sebillis I was in a group and I needed to leave.  I told the group I had to go and I immediately received 3 private tells from people within the group saying &quot;please dont leave we need you&quot;. One of the people in the group went so far as to say, &quot;Please dont go you are what is holding the group together...without you we will have to head to the exit.&quot;  <br>
<br>
That has never happened with my mage. Normally if I try to form a group people join and see that I am a mage and disband.  That is the honest to god truth.  I have friends so I dont go groupless for long but that really isnt the point. The Mage vs. Offense Melee debate is complicated. I wont go into all the details but one of the major drawbacks of a 56+ mage is the lack of a epic. I know there are alot of lvl 55 and below magicians that have been able to get there epic but this isnt the norm.  Most magicians dont have there epic and those that get them are lvl 60.  I am lvl 56 and most of the rogues on my server have there epic at that lvl. I would venture to say 2 out of every 3 rogues that are 56+ on my server have there epic weapon, and I would say 1 out of every 3 monks have there epic over lvl 56.  A offensive melee with a epic is going to out damage a non-epic mage.  When a group sees a 56 rogue with epic and a 56 magician without one the rogue gets picked. Same happens with monks. Verant doesnt seem to understand this. Our epic is way to difficult and it is one of the reasons magicians are lagging so far behind. Really cant compare a lvl 56-60 magician without epic to a lvl 56-60 rogue/monk that has there epic.  Epics are far from the best weapons out there now and even lowbie guilds are getting there monks/wizards/rogues/shaman/druids/enchanters outfitted with them. Magicians fall way short in this area because there are so few epic magicians in the game.  This is one of the major reasons magicians have a hard time getting a group compared to a offensive melee.<br>
<br>
Then there are perception issues that have to do with pet experience taking, magician damage output, people's fear of pet causing a wipe out.  Then there is the fact that magicians lack in alot of areas and really need damage upgrades as well as pet upgrades. When you add all these things together this is why magicians are lacking when it comes to group finding. You make your own groups and that is great but it isnt so easy for alot of magicians. Most people believe it is better to take a lvl 56 rogue non-epic over a 56 mage non-epic because they feel the rogue will do more damage then the mage. This might not be true but it is the perception that is out there. Also I have to say that even tho when I am in a group as my mage i feel i am doing a great amount of damage. When i group with a mage as my bard I dont see things dropping as fast as they would if we had a rogue.<br>
<br>
I said all that to say this...if a lvl 56 rogue is LFG and has epic and a non-epic magician is sitting LFG even if they are in comparable gear the rogue will get picked over the mage 19 out of 20 times. Magicians dont offer what other classes offer and at the end of the day that is really what counts. People pick what they feel is going to best help them in a pickup group and more times then not a magician will help alot less then another pc looking for group.  You can clean that up with fancy words and lectures but it wont change the fact that magicians are inferior to just about ever offensive melee in the game so there is no reason to pick a magician over a monk/range/rogue. They are inferior to every utility class in the game so there is no reason to pick a mage over a enchanter/shaman/bard. Pets cannot tank well and cant taunt so there is no reason to pick a mage over a warrior/SK/paladin.<br>
<br>
People compare Necromancers to Magicians but it isnt a fair comparison. Necromancers are great in groups and I have seen necromancers out do bards when it comes to crowd control.  Also with the new group mana drain, there dots, nukes and healing ability they are great. The new sta and ac buffs they have rock and twitching is a faster and more mana efficient form of mana transfer because the necromancer can keep it up alot longer then a mage can summon mod rods. Also slow vs undead and powerful undead dots makes them alot more group friendly then magicians. They just suffer from a very bad perception and I dont see many necros LFG anymore. The sad part about magicians most of what people think about them is true. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=163.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=163.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showMessageRange?topicID=163.topic&start=61&stop=67>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=163.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=163.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=163.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=163.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=htt